HEADWORD: Acrodont
<hw>Ac"ro*dont</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'a`kros</grk> summit + <grk>'odoy`s</grk>, <grk>'odo`ntos</grk>, a
tooth.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of a group of lizards having
the teeth immovably united to the top of the alveolar ridge.</def> --
<def2><pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to the
acrodonts.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

